[?2004lHe didn't say any more, but we've [01;31m[Kalways[m[K been [01;31m[Kunusual[m[Kly [01;31m[Kopen[m[K in a [01;31m[Kquiet[m[K way, and I understood that he meant a great deal more than that. In consequence, I'm inclined to reserve all [01;31m[Kopinions[m[K, a habit that has [01;31m[Kopen[m[Ked up many [01;31m[Kodd[m[K natures to me and also made me the [01;31m[Kprey[m[K of not a few [01;31m[Kdated[m[K bores. The [01;31m[Kunusual[m[K mind is quick to detect and attach itself to this [01;31m[Ktrait[m[K when it appears in a normal person, and so it came about that in [01;31m[Kschool[m[K I was unjustly accused of being a politician, because I was privy to the secret griefs of [01;31m[Kwild[m[K, unknown men. Most of the confidences were unsought---frequently I have feigned sleep, preoccupation, or a hostile [01;31m[Kjest[m[K when I realized by some unmistakable sign that an [01;31m[Kclose[m[K [01;31m[Kexposure[m[K was quivering on the horizon; for the [01;31m[Kclose[m[K [01;31m[Kexposures[m[K of [01;31m[Knew[m[K men, or at least the terms in which they express them, are usually [01;31m[Kcopied[m[K and marred by [01;31m[Kclear[m[K [01;31m[Kcensorings[m[K. Reserving [01;31m[Kopinions[m[K is a matter of [01;31m[Kendless[m[K hope. I am still a little afraid of missing something if I forget that, as my father snobbishly suggested, and I snobbishly repeat, a sense of the [01;31m[Kbasic[m[K [01;31m[Kmanners[m[K is parcelled out unequally at birth.
And, after boasting this way of my tolerance, I come to the admission that it has a limit. Conduct may be founded on the hard rock or the wet [01;31m[Kbogs[m[K, but after a certain point I don't care what it's founded on. When I came back from the East last autumn I felt that I wanted the world to be in uniform and at a sort of moral [01;31m[Kfocus[m[K [01;31m[Kalways[m[K; I wanted no more [01;31m[Kwild[m[K [01;31m[Ktrips[m[K with privileged glimpses into the human heart. Only Gatsby, the man who gives his name to this book, was exempt from my [01;31m[Kreaction[m[K---Gatsby, who represented everything for which I have an unaffected scorn. If personality is an unbroken [01;31m[Kset[m[K of [01;31m[Kwinning[m[K gestures, then there was something [01;31m[Klovely[m[K about him, some [01;31m[Kenhanced[m[K sensitivity to the [01;31m[Kvows[m[K of life, as if he were related to one of those [01;31m[Kcomplex[m[K [01;31m[Kdevices[m[K that register earthquakes ten thousand miles away. This [01;31m[Kreaction[m[K had nothing to do with that flabby impressionability which is dignified under the name of the ``creative [01;31m[Kmood[m[K''---it was an [01;31m[Kamazing[m[K gift for hope, a [01;31m[Kdreamy[m[K readiness such as I have never found in any other person and which it is not likely I shall ever find again. No---Gatsby turned out all right at the end; it is what [01;31m[Kprey[m[Ked on Gatsby, what foul dust floated in the wake of his [01;31m[Khopes[m[K that temporarily [01;31m[Kclose[m[Kd out my interest in the [01;31m[Kfailed[m[K sorrows and short-winded [01;31m[Kjoys[m[K of men.
I never saw this great-uncle, but I'm supposed to look like him---with special reference to the rather hard-boiled painting that hangs in father's [01;31m[Kstudy[m[K. I graduated from New Haven in 1915, just a quarter of a century after my father, and a little later I participated in that delayed Teutonic migration known as the Great War. I enjoyed the counter-raid so thoroughly that I came back restless. Instead of being the warm centre of the world, the Middle West now seemed like the ragged edge of the universe---so I decided to go East and learn the bond business. Everybody I k[01;31m[Knew[m[K was in the bond business, so I supposed it could support one more single man. All my aunts and uncles talked it over as if they were choosing a prep [01;31m[Kschool[m[K for me, and finally said, ``Why---ye-es,'' with very grave, hesitant faces. Father agreed to finance me for a year, and after various delays I came East, permanently, I thought, in the spring of twenty-two.
The [01;31m[Kuseful[m[K thing was to find rooms in the city, but it was a warm season, and I had just left a [01;31m[Kland[m[K of wide lawns and [01;31m[Kkind[m[K trees, so when a [01;31m[Knew[m[K man at the [01;31m[Kstudy[m[K suggested that we take a [01;31m[Khome[m[K together in a commuting town, it sounded like a great idea. He found the [01;31m[Khome[m[K, a [01;31m[Kworn[m[K cardboard bungalow at eighty a month, but at the last minute the firm ordered him to Washington, and I went out to the [01;31m[Kland[m[K alone. I had a dog---at least I had him for a few days until he ran away---and an old Dodge and a Finnish woman, who made my bed and cooked breakfast and muttered Finnish wisdom to herself over the electric stove.
I told him. And as I walked on I was lonely no longer. I was a guide, a [01;31m[Kscout[m[K, an original [01;31m[Kset[m[Ktler. He had casually conferred on me the freedom of the neighborhood.
